WHO   — The Halftime Rebellion — the mutiny · the catharsis
WHAT  — The turn: the boys stop being tools, Mox takes over, Lance calls plays from the sideline, Billy Bob scores — and the coach is finished.
WHERE — VBL · Varsity Blues (1999)  Framework inputs: Varsity Blues (1999, dir. Brian Robbins, MTV Films/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film needs its catharsis — the moment the abused finally refuse the abuser and win without him.
HOW   — By laying down the coach's offense and playing their own, on their own terms.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We stopped playing for you at halftime. We won anyway. That was always the only ending worth having.

